Definition of variables in Behavior data

Variables inside beh:

  • beh['ntrials']: number of trials
  • beh['trInd']: trials index
  • beh['trInd_odd']: the index of odd trials
  • beh['trInd_even']: the index of even trials
  • beh['Trial_start_time']: time when animal enters each corridor
  • beh['Trial_end_time']: time when animal ran out each corridor
  • beh['stim_id']: ID of stimuli; 0:circle1, 1:circle2, 2:leaf1, 3:leaf2 4:leaf3, 5:leaf1_swap1, 6:leaf1_swap2
  • beh['SubjMove']: running information
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjMTime']: time stamps of running
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjMPos']: position inside corridor
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjMPosCum']: cumulative position inside VR
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjMDistCum']: almost identical with beh['SubjMove']['SubjMPosCum']
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjM_pitch']: pitch (forward) running speed
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjM_roll']: roll direction running speed
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjM_yaw']: yaw direction running speed
    • beh['SubjMove']['SubjM_pitch_cum']: total running distance. Note that it is not the same as beh['SubjMove']['SubjMPosCum'] given that we only move the VR and with a constant speed when beh['SubjMove']['SubjM_pitch'] pass a threshold
  • beh['Gray_space_time']: time when animal entered the gray space
  • beh['SoundPos']: position of sound cue
  • beh['SoundTime']: time of sound cue
  • beh['SoundTimeDelay']: time of sound cue with a delay, if delay=0, then it is the same as beh['SoundTime']
  • beh['RewTime']: time of reward delivery, these numbers only valid in the reward corridor.
  • beh['RewPos']: position of reward delivery, with NaN in the non-reward corridor.
  • beh['isRew']: boolean value indicating if the trial is a reward trial.
  • beh['WallType']: category of stimuli, but please ignore this one since it doesn't apply to our experiments
  • beh['WallIsProbe']: whether is a catch trial, but please ignore this one
  • beh['WallName']: name of stimuli in each corridor
  • beh['UniqWalls']: name of stimuli in the whole session
  • beh['LickTrind']: trial stamp of each lick
  • beh['LickTime']: time stamp of each lick
  • beh['LickPos']: positional stamp of each lick
  • beh['Lick_wallName']: corresponding stimulus of each lick
  • beh['VRpos']: position inside VR
  • beh['VRposCum']: cumulative position inside VR
  • beh['VRposTime']: time stamp for beh['VRpos'] and beh['VRposCum']
  • beh['ft']: time stamp for each neural frame
  • beh['ft_trInd']: trial stamp for each neural frame, NaN means outside the behavior recorded
  • beh['ft_trInd_odd']: neural frames from odd trials
  • beh['ft_trInd_even']: neural frames from even trials
  • beh['ft_Pos']: position inside VR for each neural frame
  • beh['ft_PosCum']: culculative position inside VR for each neural frame
  • beh['ft_move']: the differences between each frame of beh['ft_PosCum']
  • beh['ft_isMoving']: boolean value for beh['ft_move']>0
  • beh['ft_GraySpc']: boolean value indicating if animals is inside gray space
  • beh['ft_CorrSpc']: boolean value indicating if animals is inside texture area
  • beh['ft_WallID']: the corridor each neural frame belongs to
  • beh['ft_RunCum']: cumulative running distance for each neural frame
  • beh['ft_RunSpeed']: running speed for each neural frame
  • beh['RunFr']: same as beh['ft_RunSpeed']
  • beh['run_pos']: running speed interpolated into trials * positions
  • beh['RewardFr']: neural frame when reward was delivered, length=ntrials, NaN means trial without reward being delivered
  • beh['StartFr']: neural frame when animal enter each corridor
  • beh['GrayFr']: neural frame when animal enter gray space
  • beh['EndFr']: neural frame when animal ran out of a corridor
  • beh['LickFr']: neural frame when animal licked
  • beh['SoundFr']: neural frame when sound cue was delivered
  • beh['SoundDelayFr']: neural frame when sound cue was delivered + a delay, if delay=0, then it is the same as beh['SoundFr']
  • beh['SoundDelPos']: position inside a corridor, corresponding to beh['SoundDelayFr']
  • beh['BefCueFr']: boolean values indicating neural frames after entered corridor but before cue was delivered
  • beh['AftCueFr']: boolean values indicating neural frames after cue was delivered
  • beh['TrialStim']: stimulus name of each trial
  • beh['StimTrial']: subfields are trial index of each stimulus
  • beh['StimFrame']: subfields are neural frame index of each stimulus

Below are some settings:

  • beh['Corridor_Length']: length of the corridor
  • beh['Gray_Space_length']: length of gray space
  • beh['Texture_Length']: length of texture area
  • beh['Reward_Mode']: reward mode of experiment, either passive reward in which reward was delivered without lick or active reward in which reward was triggered be licking
  • beh['Reward_Delay_ms']: delay time for reward, this is a setting. Find the actually reward time in beh['RewTime']

# === Download only supervised files ===
for file in file_metadata['files']:
    if file['id'] in file_ID:
        fn = os.path.join(root, file['name'])
        if not os.path.isfile(fn):
            print(f" Downloading {file['name']}...")
            response = requests.get(BASE_URL + '/file/download/' + str(file['id']))
            with open(fn, 'wb') as f:
                f.write(response.content)
        else:
            print(f" Already exists: {file['name']}")


# Function For getting additional data
def download_npy_from_figshare(root, target_file, article_id=28811129):
    """
    Download a .npy file from Figshare to the specified root directory.

    Args:
        root (str): Directory where the file should be saved.
        target_file (str): Name of the .npy file to download (must match Figshare listing).
        article_id (int): Figshare article ID (default is Zhong et al., 2025: 28811129).

    Returns:
        str: Local file path to the downloaded file.
    """
    os.makedirs(root, exist_ok=True)
    FIGSHARE_API = "https://api.figshare.com/v2"

    # Get file list from Figshare
    response = requests.get(f"{FIGSHARE_API}/articles/{article_id}")
    file_list = response.json()['files']

    # Search for the target file
    file_url = None
    for f in file_list:
        if f['name'] == target_file:
            file_url = f['download_url']
            break

    if file_url is None:
        raise FileNotFoundError(f" {target_file} not found in Figshare article {article_id}.")

    # Download the file
    save_path = os.path.join(root, target_file)
    if not os.path.exists(save_path):  # Avoid re-downloading if already present
        print(f" Downloading {target_file} ...")
        r = requests.get(file_url)
        with open(save_path, 'wb') as f:
            f.write(r.content)
        print(f" Downloaded and saved to {save_path}")
    else:
        print(f" File already exists locally: {save_path}")

    return save_path

# Load Neuronal Dataset
def load_neurons_for_subject(file_path):
    """
    Returns:
        np.ndarray: Reconstructed neural activity (timepoints  neurons)
    """
    if file_path.endswith('.npy'):
        data = np.load(file_path, allow_pickle=True).item()
        if 'U' in data and 'V' in data:
            U = data['U'].T  # Transpose: (timepoints  components)
            V = data['V']    # (components  neurons)
            neural_data = U @ V  # Reconstruct: (timepoints  neurons)
        else:
            raise ValueError(f"Error in {file_path}")

    elif file_path.endswith('.npz'):
        data = np.load(file_path, allow_pickle=True)
        var_name = [key for key in data.keys() if 'rec' in key][0]
        neural_data = data[var_name]

    else:
        raise ValueError("File must be a .npy or .npz")

    print(f" Loaded and reconstructed neural data from: {file_path}")
    print(f"Shape (timepoints  neurons): {neural_data.shape}")
    return neural_data

import pandas as pd
def load_and_preprocess(csv_path, stimulus_filter = None):
  print(f"\nLoading {csv_path} ...")
  df = pd.read_csv(csv_path)

  if stimulus_filter:
    df = df[df['stimulus']== stimulus_filter]

  df = df.reset_index(drop=True) # Reset Index

  df['lickFrames'] = df['lickFrames'].apply(
      lambda x: ast.literal_eval(x) if isinstance(x, str) else x
  )
  print(f" Finished preprocessing | Shape: {df.shape}")


  return df
#####
def clean_trials(lick_df):
    """
    Args: lick_df (pd.DataFrame): Lick trial dataframe.

    Returns: pd.DataFrame: Cleaned trials dataframe. list: Skipped trial numbers. list: Issue trial numbers.
    """
    skipped_trials, issue_trials, cleaned_trials = [], [], []
    print(f"\n Cleaning Dataset| Shape of Dataframe (pre): {lick_df.shape}")

    for idx in range(len(lick_df)):
        trial = lick_df.iloc[idx]
        trial_lick_frames = trial['lickFrames']

        # Case 1: No licks recorded
        if len(trial_lick_frames) == 0:
            print(f"[Skipped] Trial index {idx} (TrialNumber {trial['trialNumber']}): No licks recorded.")
            skipped_trials.append(trial['trialNumber'])
            continue

        # Case 2: Last lick < reward frame
        if trial_lick_frames[-1] < trial['rewardFrame']:
            print(
                f"[Issue] Trial index {idx} (TrialNumber {trial['trialNumber']}): "
                f"Last lick ({trial_lick_frames[-1]}) < Reward frame ({trial['rewardFrame']})"
            )
            issue_trials.append(trial['trialNumber'])
            continue

        # Otherwise: keep trial
        cleaned_trials.append(trial)

    cleaned_subject_trials = pd.DataFrame(cleaned_trials)

    #  Summary
    total_tossed = len(skipped_trials) + len(issue_trials)
    print(" Cleaning Complete")
    print(f"Shape of Cleaned Dataframe (post): {cleaned_subject_trials.shape}")
    print(f"Total trials tossed: {total_tossed}")
    #print(f"Skipped Trials (no licks): {skipped_trials}")
    #print(f"Issue Trials (last lick < reward frame): {issue_trials}")
    print(f"Remaining trials: {cleaned_subject_trials.shape[0]}\n")

    return cleaned_subject_trials, skipped_trials, issue_trials

def extract_antic_nonantic_activity(neural_data,cleaned_trials,window = 3):
  '''Extracts anticipatory & non-anticipatory activity from neural data.
    Args:
        neural_data (np.ndarray): Shape (n_neurons, n_frames)
        cleaned_trials (pd.DataFrame): Pre-cleaned trials with lickFrames
        window (int): Number of frames to include before each lick

    Returns:
      tuple: (antic_activity, non_antic_activity), each (trials  neurons  frames)  '''

  trial_ant_act, trial_non_act = [], []
  max_frame = neural_data.shape[1] - 1  # The max frame index

  print("\n Extracting Anticipatory & Non-Anticipatory Activity")
  print(f"Neural Data Shape (input): {neural_data.shape}")
  print(f"Total Cleaned Trials: {cleaned_trials.shape[0]}\n")

  for i in range(len(cleaned_trials)):
    trial = cleaned_trials.iloc[i] # loop through trials
    trial_lick_frames = trial['lickFrames']

    trial_antic_lick = int(trial_lick_frames[0]) # first lick
    trial_n_antic_lick = int(trial_lick_frames[-1]) # last lick

    # Safe frame windows (avoid exceeding max_frame)
    antic_frames = [f for f in range(trial_antic_lick - window, trial_antic_lick) # frames in window before antic lick
                    if 0 <= f <= max_frame] # range of the specified frames for first lick !> than max or less than 0
    non_antic_frames = [f for f in range(trial_n_antic_lick - window, trial_n_antic_lick) # frames in window before non-antic lick
                        if 0 <= f <= max_frame] # range of the specified frames for last lick !> than max or less than 0

    # Skip incomplete windows
    if len(antic_frames) != window or len(non_antic_frames) != window:
      print(f" Skipping Trial {trial['trialNumber']} (Index {i}): "
          f"antic_frames={len(antic_frames)}/{window}, "
          f"non_antic_frames={len(non_antic_frames)}/{window}, "
          f"lickFrames={trial_lick_frames}, "
          f"rewardFrame={trial['rewardFrame']}")
      continue

    # Slice neural activity (neurons  frames)
    trial_ant_act.append(neural_data[:, antic_frames])
    trial_non_act.append(neural_data[:, non_antic_frames])

  trial_ant_act = np.stack(trial_ant_act)  # anticipatory activity list
  trial_non_act = np.stack(trial_non_act) # non-anticipatory activity list

  print(f"\n Finished Processing {trial_ant_act.shape[0]} Trials")
  print(f"Anticipatory Activity Shape: {trial_ant_act.shape}")
  print(f"Non-Anticipatory Activity Shape: {trial_non_act.shape}")

  return trial_ant_act, trial_non_act

def match_neural_to_trials(neural_data, cleaned_trials):
    # Filters neural data to keep only frames from cleaned trials.

    valid_trial_ids = cleaned_trials['trialNumber'].values.astype(int)
    neural_data_cleaned = neural_data[valid_trial_ids, :]
    print(f"\n Neural Data Matched to Cleaned Trials: {neural_data_cleaned.shape}")
    return neural_data_cleaned

# Function For getting additional data
def download_npy_from_figshare(root, target_file, article_id=28811129):
    """
    Download a .npy file from Figshare to the specified root directory.

    Args:
        root (str): Directory where the file should be saved.
        target_file (str): Name of the .npy file to download (must match Figshare listing).
        article_id (int): Figshare article ID (default is Zhong et al., 2025: 28811129).

    Returns:
        str: Local file path to the downloaded file.
    """
    os.makedirs(root, exist_ok=True)
    FIGSHARE_API = "https://api.figshare.com/v2"

    # Get file list from Figshare
    response = requests.get(f"{FIGSHARE_API}/articles/{article_id}")
    file_list = response.json()['files']

    # Search for the target file
    file_url = None
    for f in file_list:
        if f['name'] == target_file:
            file_url = f['download_url']
            break

    if file_url is None:
        raise FileNotFoundError(f" {target_file} not found in Figshare article {article_id}.")

    # Download the file
    save_path = os.path.join(root, target_file)
    if not os.path.exists(save_path):  # Avoid re-downloading if already present
        print(f" Downloading {target_file} ...")
        r = requests.get(file_url)
        with open(save_path, 'wb') as f:
            f.write(r.content)
        print(f" Downloaded and saved to {save_path}")
    else:
        print(f" File already exists locally: {save_path}")

    return save_path

print(f"Shape of Anticipatory Means: {antic_means.shape}", f"\nShape of Non-Anticipatory means: {non_antic_means.shape}")  # Expect (132, n_neurons)

# Functions for Calculating Cohens D
def calculate_d(avg_neurons_a, avg_neurons_n, eps=1e-8):
    """Calculate Cohen's d' for each neuron with numerical stability."""
    u1 = np.nanmean(avg_neurons_a, axis=0)
    u2 = np.nanmean(avg_neurons_n, axis=0)
    sig1 = np.nanstd(avg_neurons_a, axis=0)
    sig2 = np.nanstd(avg_neurons_n, axis=0)
    d = 2 * (u1 - u2) / (sig1 + sig2)
    return d # Returns an array of d values

def cohen_d_pipeline(antic_means, non_antic_means, threshold=0.2, bin_size=40, animal_id="TX108"):
    """
    Full pipeline: calculates Cohen's d, thresholds neurons, and visualizes results.
    """
    # --- 1) Compute Cohen's d ---
    d = calculate_d(antic_means, non_antic_means) # uses function above
    antic_selective = d >= threshold # get selective anticipatory booleans
    non_selective = d <= -threshold # get selective non-anticipatory booleans
    neutral = (d > -threshold) & (d < threshold) # get nonselective (neutral) booleans

    antic_count = antic_selective.sum() # number of
    non_count = non_selective.sum() # number of
    neutral_count = neutral.sum() # number of

    print(f"\n Cohen's d Calculated for {len(d)} neurons")
    print(f"Anticipatory-selective: {antic_count}")
    print(f"Non-anticipatory-selective: {non_count}")
    print(f"Neutral: {neutral_count}")

    # ================================
    # --- Combined Bar + Pie Chart ---
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 5))

    # --- BAR CHART (Proportions) ---
    total = antic_count + non_count + neutral_count
    proportions = [antic_count / total, non_count / total, neutral_count / total]
    labels = ['Anticipatory', 'Non-anticipatory', 'Neutral']
    colors = ['orange', 'blue', 'gray']

    bars = axes[0].bar(labels, proportions, color=colors)
    for bar, count in zip(bars, [antic_count, non_count, neutral_count]):
        axes[0].text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, bar.get_height(),
                     f"{count}", ha='center', va='bottom')
    axes[0].set_ylabel("Proportion of Neurons")
    axes[0].set_title(f"Neuron Selectivity Groups (Threshold={threshold})")

    # --- PIE CHART WITH COUNTS (IN THE SAME FIGURE) ---
    counts = [antic_count, non_count, neutral_count]
    pie_labels = [
        f"Anticipatory\n(n={antic_count})",
        f"Non-anticipatory\n(n={non_count})",
        f"Neutral\n(n={neutral_count})"
    ]
    axes[1].pie(
        counts,
        labels=pie_labels,
        colors=colors,
        autopct='%1.1f%%',
        startangle=90
    )
    axes[1].set_title(f"Neuron Selectivity Groups\n(Cohen's d | {animal_id})")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # ======================
    # --- SPLIT HISTOS ---
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(10, 4))
    axs[0].hist(d[antic_selective], bins=30, color='orange')
    axs[0].set_title("Anticipatory-selective Neurons")
    axs[0].set_xlabel("Cohen's d")
    axs[0].set_ylabel("Count")

    axs[1].hist(d[non_selective], bins=30, color='blue')
    axs[1].set_title("Non-anticipatory-selective Neurons")
    axs[1].set_xlabel("Cohen's d")
    axs[1].set_ylabel("Count")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # ================================
    # --- 4) CLASSIC HISTOGRAM OVERLAY (Counts + Threshold Lines) ---
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
    plt.hist(d[antic_selective], bins=40, color='orange', alpha=0.7,
             label=f'Anticipatory (n={antic_count})')
    plt.hist(d[non_selective], bins=40, color='blue', alpha=0.7,
             label=f'Non-anticipatory (n={non_count})')
    plt.hist(d[neutral], bins=7, color='gray', alpha=0.5,
             label=f'Neutral (n={neutral_count})')

    plt.axvline(threshold, color='black', linestyle='--')
    plt.axvline(-threshold, color='black', linestyle='--')
    plt.xlabel("Cohen's d")
    plt.xlim(-5, 5)
    plt.xticks(np.arange(-5, 6, 1))
    plt.ylabel("Neuron Count")
    plt.title(f"Distribution of Neuronal Counts (Threshold = {threshold}) | {animal_id}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

        # ================================
    # --- 5) MEAN NEURAL ACTIVITY DISTRIBUTIONS ---
    antic_neuron_means = antic_means.mean(axis=0)        # (n_neurons,)
    non_antic_neuron_means = non_antic_means.mean(axis=0) # (n_neurons,)

    # --- 2) Select only neurons above threshold ---
    selected_antic_means = antic_neuron_means[antic_selective]
    selected_non_antic_means = non_antic_neuron_means[non_selective]

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
    plt.hist(selected_antic_means, bins=40, color='orange', alpha=0.6, label='Anticipatory')
    plt.hist(selected_non_antic_means, bins=40, color='blue', alpha=0.6, label='Non-anticipatory')
    plt.xlabel("Mean Neural Activity per Neuron (F/F)")
    plt.ylabel("Neuron Count")
    plt.title(f"Mean Activity of Selective Neurons (|Cohen's d|  {threshold})")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    return d, antic_selective, non_selective, neutral


def threshold_sensitivity(d, chosen_threshold=0.2):
    thresholds = np.linspace(0.05, 0.5, 10)
    counts = [np.sum((d >= t) | (d <= -t)) for t in thresholds]
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    plt.plot(thresholds, counts, 'o-', color='purple', label="Neuron Counts")
    plt.axvline(chosen_threshold, color='gray', linestyle='--', alpha=0.8, label=f"Chosen Threshold = {chosen_threshold}")
    plt.xlabel("Threshold (Cohen's d)")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Selective Neurons (|d|  threshold)")
    plt.title("Neuron Counts vs Threshold")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()


def plot_antic_vs_nonantic_activity(antic_means, non_antic_means, sample_range=None):
    """
    Plots anticipatory vs non-anticipatory mean neural activity with regression analysis.

    Args:
        antic_means (np.ndarray): Mean anticipatory activity per neuron (n_neurons,).
        non_antic_means (np.ndarray): Mean non-anticipatory activity per neuron (n_neurons,).
        sample_range (tuple or None): If provided (start, stop), restricts to this slice.

    Returns:
        slope (float), intercept (float), r_squared (float), p_value (float)
    """
    #  Optional sampling (e.g., first 100 neurons)
    if sample_range is not None:
        antic_means = antic_means[sample_range[0]:sample_range[1]]
        non_antic_means = non_antic_means[sample_range[0]:sample_range[1]]

    #  Regression analysis
    slope, intercept, r_value, p_value, _ = linregress(antic_means, non_antic_means)
    r_squared = r_value ** 2


    #  Plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 7))
    plt.scatter(antic_means, non_antic_means, s=10, color='purple', alpha=0.5)
    plt.plot(np.sort(antic_means),
             slope * np.sort(antic_means) + intercept,
             color='orange', linewidth=2, label=f"Trend (slope={slope:.2f})")
    plt.plot([min(antic_means), max(antic_means)],
             [min(antic_means), max(antic_means)],
             'k--', label="y = x (Equal Activity)")
    plt.xlabel("Anticipatory Mean Activity (F/F)")
    plt.ylabel("Non-Anticipatory Mean Activity (F/F)")
    plt.title(f"Neuron Activity Relationship\n(Anticipatory vs Non-Anticipatory) {animal_id}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    print(f"Slope: {slope:.3f}, R: {r_squared:.3f}, p={p_value:.3e}")

    return slope, intercept, r_squared, p_value

#@title *=== Regional Selectivity Functions===*
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os
import seaborn as sns
def visualize_d_overlay(trans_path,
                        d_values,
                        antic_mask,
                        non_antic_mask,
                        neutral_mask,
                        animal_id="Unknown",
                        lim=None,
                        use_sub_regions=False):
    if lim is None:
        lim = get_auto_lim(trans_path)

    trans_data = np.load(trans_path, allow_pickle=True)
    mapping = sub_area_names_mapping if use_sub_regions else area_mapping

    df = pd.DataFrame({
        'x': trans_data['xpos'][lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]],
        'y': trans_data['ypos'][lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]],
        'region': pd.Series(trans_data['iarea'][lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]]).map(mapping),
        'd': d_values[lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]],
        'state': np.select(
            [antic_mask[lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]],
             non_antic_mask[lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]],
             neutral_mask[lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]]],
            ['Anticipatory', 'Non-Anticipatory', 'Neutral'],
            default='Other'
        )
    })

    # Plot by state
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
    sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='x', y='y', hue='state', s=5,
                    palette={'Anticipatory': 'red', 'Non-Anticipatory': 'blue', 'Neutral': 'gray'})
    plt.title(f"Cohen's d & State Overlay: {animal_id}")
    plt.show()

    return df


def quantify_region_selectivity(trans_path,
                                selectivity_mask,
                                animal_id="Unknown",
                                lim=None,
                                use_sub_regions=True,
                                label="Anticipatory",
                                plot=True):
    """
    Quantifies the proportion AND raw counts of neurons per region that meet a selectivity condition.
    Returns a DataFrame with columns: ['region', 'count', 'total', 'proportion'].
    """
    mapping = sub_area_names_mapping if use_sub_regions else area_mapping

    # Auto-detect lim if not provided
    if lim is None:
        lim = get_auto_lim(trans_path)

    trans_data = np.load(trans_path, allow_pickle=True)
    df = pd.DataFrame({
        'region': pd.Series(trans_data['iarea'][lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]]).map(mapping)
    })

    # Assign descriptive labels for selectivity
    df['selectivity'] = np.where(selectivity_mask[lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]], label, f"Not {label}")

    # Compute raw counts and proportions per region
    summary = (
        df.groupby('region')
        .apply(lambda g: pd.Series({
            'count': (g['selectivity'] == label).sum(),
            'total': len(g),
            'proportion': (g['selectivity'] == label).sum() / len(g)
        }))
        .reset_index()
    )

    # Plot proportions if requested
    if plot:
        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
        sns.barplot(data=summary, x='region', y='proportion',
                    order=summary.sort_values('proportion', ascending=False)['region'])
        plt.title(f"Proportion of {label} Neurons per Region ({animal_id})")
        plt.ylabel(f"Proportion ({label} / Total)")
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

    print(f" Quantified {animal_id}: {len(df)} neurons analyzed ({label}).")
    return summary

# Now plot a histo with combined antic and non-antic proportions normalized for total
def plot_antic_vs_nonantic(trans_path, antic_mask, non_antic_mask,
                           animal_id="Unknown", use_sub_regions=True):
    """
    Plots the proportion of anticipatory vs non-anticipatory neurons per region.
    """
    # === Choose mapping ===
    mapping = sub_area_names_mapping if use_sub_regions else area_mapping

    # === Load transformation data ===
    trans_data = np.load(trans_path, allow_pickle=True)
    n_neurons = trans_data['xpos'].shape[0]
    regions = pd.Series(trans_data['iarea']).map(mapping)

    # === Build DataFrame with labels ===
    df = pd.DataFrame({'region': regions})
    df['antic'] = antic_mask[:n_neurons]
    df['non_antic'] = non_antic_mask[:n_neurons]

    # === Summarize proportions per region ===
    summary = (
        df.groupby('region')
        .apply(lambda g: pd.Series({
            'proportion_antic': g['antic'].sum() / len(g),
            'proportion_non_antic': g['non_antic'].sum() / len(g)
        }))
        .reset_index()
    )

    # === Melt for plotting (long format) ===
    plot_df = summary.melt(id_vars='region',
                           value_vars=['proportion_antic', 'proportion_non_antic'],
                           var_name='Type', value_name='Proportion')

    # Clean up labels
    plot_df['Type'] = plot_df['Type'].replace({
        'proportion_antic': 'Anticipatory',
        'proportion_non_antic': 'Non-Anticipatory'
    })

    # === Plot ===
    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 6))
    sns.barplot(data=plot_df, x='region', y='Proportion', hue='Type',
                order=summary.sort_values('proportion_antic', ascending=False)['region'],
                palette=['gold', 'blue'])

    plt.title(f"Proportion of Anticipatory vs Non-Anticipatory Neurons per Region ({animal_id})")
    plt.ylabel("Proportion (Normalized by Total Neurons in Region)")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Neuron Type")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    return summary

# @title *=== Data Flatten, PCA Visualize, t-SNE Function ===*
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

def pca_flattened_vs_avg(ant_act, non_ant_act, n_components=2, animal_id="Unknown", scale=False):
  '''
  Runs PCA on flattened & averaged data
  '''
  # Combine Data
  X_all = np.concatenate([ant_act, non_ant_act], axis = 0)
  print(f"Shape of X_all = {X_all.shape}")
  labels = np.concatenate([np.ones(len(ant_act)), np.zeros(len(non_ant_act))])
  print(f"Shape of labels = {labels.shape}")

  print("PCA running...")
  # === Flattened Representation ===
  X_flat = X_all.reshape(X_all.shape[0], -1)
  if scale:
      X_flat = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X_flat)
  pca_model_flat = PCA(n_components=n_components)
  pca_flat = pca_model_flat.fit_transform(X_flat)

  # === Averaged Representation ===
  X_avg = X_all.mean(axis=2)
  if scale:
      X_avg = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X_avg)
  pca_model_avg = PCA(n_components=n_components)
  pca_avg = pca_model_avg.fit_transform(X_avg)


  # === Visualization ===
  fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))

  scatter1 = axs[0].scatter(
      pca_flat[:, 0], pca_flat[:, 1],
      c=labels, cmap='coolwarm', edgecolor='black', s=40, alpha=0.85
  )
  axs[0].set_title(f"{animal_id} PCA: Flattened Neuron  Time", fontsize=12, weight='bold')
  axs[0].set_xlabel("PC1", fontsize=11)
  axs[0].set_ylabel("PC2", fontsize=11)
  axs[0].grid(alpha=0.3)

  scatter2 = axs[1].scatter(
      pca_avg[:, 0], pca_avg[:, 1],
      c=labels, cmap='coolwarm', edgecolor='black', s=40, alpha=0.85
  )
  axs[1].set_title(f"{animal_id} PCA: Averaged Across Time", fontsize=12, weight='bold')
  axs[1].set_xlabel("PC1", fontsize=11)
  axs[1].set_ylabel("PC2", fontsize=11)
  axs[1].grid(alpha=0.3)

  # --- Shared Colorbar (Forced Further to Right) ---
  cbar = fig.colorbar(
      scatter2,
      ax=axs,
      orientation='vertical',
      fraction=0.046,  # thickness of the bar
      pad=0.04         # <-- increase this to push further right (default ~0.04)
  )
  cbar.set_ticks([0, 1])
  cbar.set_ticklabels(['Non-anticipatory', 'Anticipatory'])

  plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 0.86, 1])  #  give more space for the bar
  plt.show()

  return {
      "X_flat": X_flat, # (n_trials, n_neurons * n_timepoints) = flattened trial data (neurons x time collapsed to 1d)
      "pca_flat": pca_flat, #  (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for flatt input
      "pca_model_flat": pca_model_flat,   # PCA object containing explained variance
      "X_avg": X_avg,  # (n_trials, n_neurons) = time avg activity per trials (means across frames)
      "pca_avg": pca_avg, # (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for avg input
      "pca_model_avg": pca_model_avg,     # PCA object = containing the explained_variance_ratio_ and components_ for avg PCA
      "labels": labels #(n_trials) = 1 = antic trials | 0 = non-antic trials
  }

from sklearn.manifold import TSNE
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def tsne_from_existing_pca(pca_results, use="avg", tsne_perplexity=30, random_state=42, animal_id="Unknown", plot=True):
    """
    Runs t-SNE on the PCA results from `pca_flattened_vs_avg`.

    Args:
        pca_results (dict): Output from `pca_flattened_vs_avg`.
        use (str): Which data to use: "avg" (averaged across time) or "flat" (flattened neuron  time).
        tsne_perplexity (int): t-SNE perplexity.
        random_state (int): Random seed for reproducibility.
        animal_id (str): For plot title.
        plot (bool): Whether to show the t-SNE embedding.

    Returns:
        dict: {
            "X_pca": (n_trials, n_components),
            "X_tsne": (n_trials, 2),
            "labels": (n_trials,)
        }
    """

    # === Select PCA output ===
    if use == "avg":
        X_pca = pca_results["pca_avg"] # uses  (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for avg input
    elif use == "flat":
        X_pca = pca_results["pca_flat"] # uses (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for flatt input
    else:
        raise ValueError("use either 'avg' or 'flat' !")

    labels = pca_results["labels"]

    # === Run t-SNE ===
    tsne = TSNE(
        n_components=2,
        perplexity=tsne_perplexity,
        learning_rate='auto',
        init='pca',
        random_state=random_state
    )
    X_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(X_pca)

    # === Visualization ===
    if plot:
        plt.figure(figsize=(7, 6))
        sc = plt.scatter(X_tsne[:, 0], X_tsne[:, 1], c=labels, cmap='coolwarm',
                         edgecolor='k', alpha=0.8)
        plt.title(f"{animal_id} t-SNE Embedding ({'Averaged' if use=='avg' else 'Flattened'})", fontsize=12, weight='bold')
        plt.xlabel('t-SNE 1')
        plt.ylabel('t-SNE 2')
        cbar = plt.colorbar(sc)
        cbar.set_ticks([0, 1])
        cbar.set_ticklabels(['Non-anticipatory', 'Anticipatory'])
        plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

    return {
        "X_pca": X_pca,
        "X_tsne": X_tsne,
        "labels": labels
    }

# Load Neuronal Dataset
def load_neurons_for_subject(file_path):
    """
    Returns:
        np.ndarray: Reconstructed neural activity (timepoints  neurons)
    """
    if file_path.endswith('.npy'):
        data = np.load(file_path, allow_pickle=True).item()
        if 'U' in data and 'V' in data:
            U = data['U'].T  # Transpose: (timepoints  components)
            V = data['V']    # (components  neurons)
            neural_data = U @ V  # Reconstruct: (timepoints  neurons)
        else:
            raise ValueError(f"Error in {file_path}")

    elif file_path.endswith('.npz'):
        data = np.load(file_path, allow_pickle=True)
        var_name = [key for key in data.keys() if 'rec' in key][0]
        neural_data = data[var_name]

    else:
        raise ValueError("File must be a .npy or .npz")

    print(f" Loaded and reconstructed neural data from: {file_path}")
    print(f"Shape (timepoints  neurons): {neural_data.shape}")
    return neural_data

def clean_trials(lick_df):
    """
    Args: lick_df (pd.DataFrame): Lick trial dataframe.

    Returns: pd.DataFrame: Cleaned trials dataframe. list: Skipped trial numbers. list: Issue trial numbers.
    """
    skipped_trials, issue_trials, cleaned_trials = [], [], []
    print(f"\n Cleaning Dataset| Shape of Dataframe (pre): {lick_df.shape}")

    for idx in range(len(lick_df)):
        trial = lick_df.iloc[idx]
        trial_lick_frames = trial['lickFrames']

        # Case 1: No licks recorded
        if len(trial_lick_frames) == 0:
            print(f"[Skipped] Trial index {idx} (TrialNumber {trial['trialNumber']}): No licks recorded.")
            skipped_trials.append(trial['trialNumber'])
            continue

        # Case 2: Last lick < reward frame
        if trial_lick_frames[-1] < trial['rewardFrame']:
            print(
                f"[Issue] Trial index {idx} (TrialNumber {trial['trialNumber']}): "
                f"Last lick ({trial_lick_frames[-1]}) < Reward frame ({trial['rewardFrame']})"
            )
            issue_trials.append(trial['trialNumber'])
            continue

        # Otherwise: keep trial
        cleaned_trials.append(trial)

    cleaned_subject_trials = pd.DataFrame(cleaned_trials)

    #  Summary
    total_tossed = len(skipped_trials) + len(issue_trials)
    print(" Cleaning Complete")
    print(f"Shape of Cleaned Dataframe (post): {cleaned_subject_trials.shape}")
    print(f"Total trials tossed: {total_tossed}")
    #print(f"Skipped Trials (no licks): {skipped_trials}")
    #print(f"Issue Trials (last lick < reward frame): {issue_trials}")
    print(f"Remaining trials: {cleaned_subject_trials.shape[0]}\n")

    return cleaned_subject_trials, skipped_trials, issue_trials

def extract_antic_nonantic_activity(neural_data,cleaned_trials,window = 3):
  '''Extracts anticipatory & non-anticipatory activity from neural data.
    Args:
        neural_data (np.ndarray): Shape (n_neurons, n_frames)
        cleaned_trials (pd.DataFrame): Pre-cleaned trials with lickFrames
        window (int): Number of frames to include before each lick

    Returns:
      tuple: (antic_activity, non_antic_activity), each (trials  neurons  frames)  '''

  trial_ant_act, trial_non_act = [], []
  max_frame = neural_data.shape[1] - 1  # The max frame index

  print("\n Extracting Anticipatory & Non-Anticipatory Activity")
  print(f"Neural Data Shape (input): {neural_data.shape}")
  print(f"Total Cleaned Trials: {cleaned_trials.shape[0]}\n")

  for i in range(len(cleaned_trials)):
    trial = cleaned_trials.iloc[i] # loop through trials
    trial_lick_frames = trial['lickFrames']

    trial_antic_lick = int(trial_lick_frames[0]) # first lick
    trial_n_antic_lick = int(trial_lick_frames[-1]) # last lick

    # Safe frame windows (avoid exceeding max_frame)
    antic_frames = [f for f in range(trial_antic_lick - window, trial_antic_lick) # frames in window before antic lick
                    if 0 <= f <= max_frame] # range of the specified frames for first lick !> than max or less than 0
    non_antic_frames = [f for f in range(trial_n_antic_lick - window, trial_n_antic_lick) # frames in window before non-antic lick
                        if 0 <= f <= max_frame] # range of the specified frames for last lick !> than max or less than 0

    # Skip incomplete windows
    if len(antic_frames) != window or len(non_antic_frames) != window:
      print(f" Skipping Trial {trial['trialNumber']} (Index {i}): "
          f"antic_frames={len(antic_frames)}/{window}, "
          f"non_antic_frames={len(non_antic_frames)}/{window}, "
          f"lickFrames={trial_lick_frames}, "
          f"rewardFrame={trial['rewardFrame']}")
      continue

    # Slice neural activity (neurons  frames)
    trial_ant_act.append(neural_data[:, antic_frames])
    trial_non_act.append(neural_data[:, non_antic_frames])

  trial_ant_act = np.stack(trial_ant_act)  # anticipatory activity list
  trial_non_act = np.stack(trial_non_act) # non-anticipatory activity list

  print(f"\n Finished Processing {trial_ant_act.shape[0]} Trials")
  print(f"Anticipatory Activity Shape: {trial_ant_act.shape}")
  print(f"Non-Anticipatory Activity Shape: {trial_non_act.shape}")

  return trial_ant_act, trial_non_act

def match_neural_to_trials(neural_data, cleaned_trials):
    # Filters neural data to keep only frames from cleaned trials.

    valid_trial_ids = cleaned_trials['trialNumber'].values.astype(int)
    neural_data_cleaned = neural_data[valid_trial_ids, :]
    print(f"\n Neural Data Matched to Cleaned Trials: {neural_data_cleaned.shape}")
    return neural_data_cleaned


# Function For getting additional data
def download_npy_from_figshare(root, target_file, article_id=28811129):
    """
    Download a .npy file from Figshare to the specified root directory.

    Args:
        root (str): Directory where the file should be saved.
        target_file (str): Name of the .npy file to download (must match Figshare listing).
        article_id (int): Figshare article ID (default is Zhong et al., 2025: 28811129).

    Returns:
        str: Local file path to the downloaded file.
    """
    os.makedirs(root, exist_ok=True)
    FIGSHARE_API = "https://api.figshare.com/v2"

    # Get file list from Figshare
    response = requests.get(f"{FIGSHARE_API}/articles/{article_id}")
    file_list = response.json()['files']

    # Search for the target file
    file_url = None
    for f in file_list:
        if f['name'] == target_file:
            file_url = f['download_url']
            break

    if file_url is None:
        raise FileNotFoundError(f" {target_file} not found in Figshare article {article_id}.")

    # Download the file
    save_path = os.path.join(root, target_file)
    if not os.path.exists(save_path):  # Avoid re-downloading if already present
        print(f" Downloading {target_file} ...")
        r = requests.get(file_url)
        with open(save_path, 'wb') as f:
            f.write(r.content)
        print(f" Downloaded and saved to {save_path}")
    else:
        print(f" File already exists locally: {save_path}")

    return save_path

# @title *Calculate Signifigance Analysis Functions (cohen's d)*
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import linregress

# Functions for Calculating Cohens D
def calculate_d(avg_neurons_a, avg_neurons_n, eps=1e-8):
    """Calculate Cohen's d' for each neuron with numerical stability."""
    u1 = np.nanmean(avg_neurons_a, axis=0)
    u2 = np.nanmean(avg_neurons_n, axis=0)
    sig1 = np.nanstd(avg_neurons_a, axis=0)
    sig2 = np.nanstd(avg_neurons_n, axis=0)
    d = 2 * (u1 - u2) / (sig1 + sig2)
    return d # Returns an array of d values

def cohen_d_pipeline(antic_means, non_antic_means, threshold=0.2, bin_size=40, animal_id="TX108"):
    """
    Full pipeline: calculates Cohen's d, thresholds neurons, and visualizes results.
    """
    # --- 1) Compute Cohen's d ---
    d = calculate_d(antic_means, non_antic_means) # uses function above
    antic_selective = d >= threshold # get selective anticipatory booleans
    non_selective = d <= -threshold # get selective non-anticipatory booleans
    neutral = (d > -threshold) & (d < threshold) # get nonselective (neutral) booleans

    antic_count = antic_selective.sum() # number of
    non_count = non_selective.sum() # number of
    neutral_count = neutral.sum() # number of

    print(f"\n Cohen's d Calculated for {len(d)} neurons")
    print(f"Anticipatory-selective: {antic_count}")
    print(f"Non-anticipatory-selective: {non_count}")
    print(f"Neutral: {neutral_count}")

    # ================================
    # --- Combined Bar + Pie Chart ---
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 5))

    # --- BAR CHART (Proportions) ---
    total = antic_count + non_count + neutral_count
    proportions = [antic_count / total, non_count / total, neutral_count / total]
    labels = ['Anticipatory', 'Non-anticipatory', 'Neutral']
    colors = ['orange', 'blue', 'gray']

    bars = axes[0].bar(labels, proportions, color=colors)
    for bar, count in zip(bars, [antic_count, non_count, neutral_count]):
        axes[0].text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, bar.get_height(),
                     f"{count}", ha='center', va='bottom')
    axes[0].set_ylabel("Proportion of Neurons")
    axes[0].set_title(f"Neuron Selectivity Groups (Threshold={threshold})")

    # --- PIE CHART WITH COUNTS (IN THE SAME FIGURE) ---
    counts = [antic_count, non_count, neutral_count]
    pie_labels = [
        f"Anticipatory\n(n={antic_count})",
        f"Non-anticipatory\n(n={non_count})",
        f"Neutral\n(n={neutral_count})"
    ]
    axes[1].pie(
        counts,
        labels=pie_labels,
        colors=colors,
        autopct='%1.1f%%',
        startangle=90
    )
    axes[1].set_title(f"Neuron Selectivity Groups\n(Cohen's d | {animal_id})")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # ======================
    # --- SPLIT HISTOS ---
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(10, 4))
    axs[0].hist(d[antic_selective], bins=30, color='orange')
    axs[0].set_title("Anticipatory-selective Neurons")
    axs[0].set_xlabel("Cohen's d")
    axs[0].set_ylabel("Count")

    axs[1].hist(d[non_selective], bins=30, color='blue')
    axs[1].set_title("Non-anticipatory-selective Neurons")
    axs[1].set_xlabel("Cohen's d")
    axs[1].set_ylabel("Count")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # ================================
    # --- 4) CLASSIC HISTOGRAM OVERLAY (Counts + Threshold Lines) ---
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
    plt.hist(d[antic_selective], bins=40, color='orange', alpha=0.7,
             label=f'Anticipatory (n={antic_count})')
    plt.hist(d[non_selective], bins=40, color='blue', alpha=0.7,
             label=f'Non-anticipatory (n={non_count})')
    plt.hist(d[neutral], bins=7, color='gray', alpha=0.5,
             label=f'Neutral (n={neutral_count})')

    plt.axvline(threshold, color='black', linestyle='--')
    plt.axvline(-threshold, color='black', linestyle='--')
    plt.xlabel("Cohen's d")
    plt.xlim(-5, 5)
    plt.xticks(np.arange(-5, 6, 1))
    plt.ylabel("Neuron Count")
    plt.title(f"Distribution of Neuronal Counts (Threshold = {threshold}) | {animal_id}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

        # ================================
    # --- 5) MEAN NEURAL ACTIVITY DISTRIBUTIONS ---
    antic_neuron_means = antic_means.mean(axis=0)        # (n_neurons,)
    non_antic_neuron_means = non_antic_means.mean(axis=0) # (n_neurons,)

    # --- 2) Select only neurons above threshold ---
    selected_antic_means = antic_neuron_means[antic_selective]
    selected_non_antic_means = non_antic_neuron_means[non_selective]

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
    plt.hist(selected_antic_means, bins=40, color='orange', alpha=0.6, label='Anticipatory')
    plt.hist(selected_non_antic_means, bins=40, color='blue', alpha=0.6, label='Non-anticipatory')
    plt.xlabel("Mean Neural Activity per Neuron (F/F)")
    plt.ylabel("Neuron Count")
    plt.title(f"Mean Activity of Selective Neurons (|Cohen's d|  {threshold})")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    return d, antic_selective, non_selective, neutral


def threshold_sensitivity(d, chosen_threshold=0.2):
    thresholds = np.linspace(0.05, 0.5, 10)
    counts = [np.sum((d >= t) | (d <= -t)) for t in thresholds]
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    plt.plot(thresholds, counts, 'o-', color='purple', label="Neuron Counts")
    plt.axvline(chosen_threshold, color='gray', linestyle='--', alpha=0.8, label=f"Chosen Threshold = {chosen_threshold}")
    plt.xlabel("Threshold (Cohen's d)")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Selective Neurons (|d|  threshold)")
    plt.title("Neuron Counts vs Threshold")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()


def plot_antic_vs_nonantic_activity(antic_means, non_antic_means, sample_range=None):
    """
    Plots anticipatory vs non-anticipatory mean neural activity with regression analysis.

    Args:
        antic_means (np.ndarray): Mean anticipatory activity per neuron (n_neurons,).
        non_antic_means (np.ndarray): Mean non-anticipatory activity per neuron (n_neurons,).
        sample_range (tuple or None): If provided (start, stop), restricts to this slice.

    Returns:
        slope (float), intercept (float), r_squared (float), p_value (float)
    """
    #  Optional sampling (e.g., first 100 neurons)
    if sample_range is not None:
        antic_means = antic_means[sample_range[0]:sample_range[1]]
        non_antic_means = non_antic_means[sample_range[0]:sample_range[1]]

    #  Regression analysis
    slope, intercept, r_value, p_value, _ = linregress(antic_means, non_antic_means)
    r_squared = r_value ** 2


    #  Plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 7))
    plt.scatter(antic_means, non_antic_means, s=10, color='purple', alpha=0.5)
    plt.plot(np.sort(antic_means),
             slope * np.sort(antic_means) + intercept,
             color='orange', linewidth=2, label=f"Trend (slope={slope:.2f})")
    plt.plot([min(antic_means), max(antic_means)],
             [min(antic_means), max(antic_means)],
             'k--', label="y = x (Equal Activity)")
    plt.xlabel("Anticipatory Mean Activity (F/F)")
    plt.ylabel("Non-Anticipatory Mean Activity (F/F)")
    plt.title("Neuron Activity Relationship\n(Anticipatory vs Non-Anticipatory)")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    print(f"Slope: {slope:.3f}, R: {r_squared:.3f}, p={p_value:.3e}")

    return slope, intercept, r_squared, p_value

def quantify_region_selectivity(trans_path,
                                selectivity_mask,
                                animal_id="Unknown",
                                lim=None,
                                use_sub_regions=True,
                                label="Anticipatory",
                                plot=True):
    """
    Quantifies the proportion AND raw counts of neurons per region that meet a selectivity condition.
    Returns a DataFrame with columns: ['region', 'count', 'total', 'proportion'].
    """
    mapping = sub_area_names_mapping if use_sub_regions else area_mapping

    # Auto-detect lim if not provided
    if lim is None:
        lim = get_auto_lim(trans_path)

    trans_data = np.load(trans_path, allow_pickle=True)
    df = pd.DataFrame({
        'region': pd.Series(trans_data['iarea'][lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]]).map(mapping)
    })

    # Assign descriptive labels for selectivity
    df['selectivity'] = np.where(selectivity_mask[lim[0]:lim[1]:lim[2]], label, f"Not {label}")

    # Compute raw counts and proportions per region
    summary = (
        df.groupby('region')
        .apply(lambda g: pd.Series({
            'count': (g['selectivity'] == label).sum(),
            'total': len(g),
            'proportion': (g['selectivity'] == label).sum() / len(g)
        }))
        .reset_index()
    )

    # Plot proportions if requested
    if plot:
        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
        sns.barplot(data=summary, x='region', y='proportion',
                    order=summary.sort_values('proportion', ascending=False)['region'])
        plt.title(f"Proportion of {label} Neurons per Region ({animal_id})")
        plt.ylabel(f"Proportion ({label} / Total)")
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

    print(f" Quantified {animal_id}: {len(df)} neurons analyzed ({label}).")
    return summary

# Now plot a histo with combined antic and non-antic proportions normalized for total
def plot_antic_vs_nonantic(trans_path, antic_mask, non_antic_mask,
                           animal_id="Unknown", use_sub_regions=True):
    """
    Plots the proportion of anticipatory vs non-anticipatory neurons per region.
    """
    # === Choose mapping ===
    mapping = sub_area_names_mapping if use_sub_regions else area_mapping

    # === Load transformation data ===
    trans_data = np.load(trans_path, allow_pickle=True)
    n_neurons = trans_data['xpos'].shape[0]
    regions = pd.Series(trans_data['iarea']).map(mapping)

    # === Build DataFrame with labels ===
    df = pd.DataFrame({'region': regions})
    df['antic'] = antic_mask[:n_neurons]
    df['non_antic'] = non_antic_mask[:n_neurons]

    # === Summarize proportions per region ===
    summary = (
        df.groupby('region')
        .apply(lambda g: pd.Series({
            'proportion_antic': g['antic'].sum() / len(g),
            'proportion_non_antic': g['non_antic'].sum() / len(g)
        }))
        .reset_index()
    )

    # === Melt for plotting (long format) ===
    plot_df = summary.melt(id_vars='region',
                           value_vars=['proportion_antic', 'proportion_non_antic'],
                           var_name='Type', value_name='Proportion')

    # Clean up labels
    plot_df['Type'] = plot_df['Type'].replace({
        'proportion_antic': 'Anticipatory',
        'proportion_non_antic': 'Non-Anticipatory'
    })

    # === Plot ===
    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 6))
    sns.barplot(data=plot_df, x='region', y='Proportion', hue='Type',
                order=summary.sort_values('proportion_antic', ascending=False)['region'],
                palette=['gold', 'blue'])

    plt.title(f"Proportion of Anticipatory vs Non-Anticipatory Neurons per Region ({animal_id})")
    plt.ylabel("Proportion (Normalized by Total Neurons in Region)")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Neuron Type")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    return summary

# @title *=== Data Flatten, PCA Visualize, t-SNE Function ===*
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

def pca_flattened_vs_avg(ant_act, non_ant_act, n_components=2, animal_id="Unknown", scale=False):
  '''
  Runs PCA on flattened & averaged data
  '''
  # Combine Data
  X_all = np.concatenate([ant_act, non_ant_act], axis = 0)
  print(f"Shape of X_all = {X_all.shape}")
  labels = np.concatenate([np.ones(len(ant_act)), np.zeros(len(non_ant_act))])
  print(f"Shape of labels = {labels.shape}")

  print("PCA running...")
  # === Flattened Representation ===
  X_flat = X_all.reshape(X_all.shape[0], -1)
  if scale:
      X_flat = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X_flat)
  pca_model_flat = PCA(n_components=n_components)
  pca_flat = pca_model_flat.fit_transform(X_flat)

  # === Averaged Representation ===
  X_avg = X_all.mean(axis=2)
  if scale:
      X_avg = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X_avg)
  pca_model_avg = PCA(n_components=n_components)
  pca_avg = pca_model_avg.fit_transform(X_avg)


  # === Visualization ===
  fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))

  scatter1 = axs[0].scatter(
      pca_flat[:, 0], pca_flat[:, 1],
      c=labels, cmap='coolwarm', edgecolor='black', s=40, alpha=0.85
  )
  axs[0].set_title(f"{animal_id} PCA: Flattened Neuron  Time", fontsize=12, weight='bold')
  axs[0].set_xlabel("PC1", fontsize=11)
  axs[0].set_ylabel("PC2", fontsize=11)
  axs[0].grid(alpha=0.3)

  scatter2 = axs[1].scatter(
      pca_avg[:, 0], pca_avg[:, 1],
      c=labels, cmap='coolwarm', edgecolor='black', s=40, alpha=0.85
  )
  axs[1].set_title(f"{animal_id} PCA: Averaged Across Time", fontsize=12, weight='bold')
  axs[1].set_xlabel("PC1", fontsize=11)
  axs[1].set_ylabel("PC2", fontsize=11)
  axs[1].grid(alpha=0.3)

  # --- Shared Colorbar (Forced Further to Right) ---
  cbar = fig.colorbar(
      scatter2,
      ax=axs,
      orientation='vertical',
      fraction=0.046,  # thickness of the bar
      pad=0.04         # <-- increase this to push further right (default ~0.04)
  )
  cbar.set_ticks([0, 1])
  cbar.set_ticklabels(['Non-anticipatory', 'Anticipatory'])

  plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 0.86, 1])  #  give more space for the bar
  plt.show()

  return {
      "X_flat": X_flat, # (n_trials, n_neurons * n_timepoints) = flattened trial data (neurons x time collapsed to 1d)
      "pca_flat": pca_flat, #  (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for flatt input
      "pca_model_flat": pca_model_flat,   # PCA object containing explained variance
      "X_avg": X_avg,  # (n_trials, n_neurons) = time avg activity per trials (means across frames)
      "pca_avg": pca_avg, # (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for avg input
      "pca_model_avg": pca_model_avg,     # PCA object = containing the explained_variance_ratio_ and components_ for avg PCA
      "labels": labels #(n_trials) = 1 = antic trials | 0 = non-antic trials
  }

from sklearn.manifold import TSNE
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def tsne_from_existing_pca(pca_results, use="avg", tsne_perplexity=30, random_state=42, animal_id="Unknown", plot=True):
    """
    Runs t-SNE on the PCA results from `pca_flattened_vs_avg`.

    Args:
        pca_results (dict): Output from `pca_flattened_vs_avg`.
        use (str): Which data to use: "avg" (averaged across time) or "flat" (flattened neuron  time).
        tsne_perplexity (int): t-SNE perplexity.
        random_state (int): Random seed for reproducibility.
        animal_id (str): For plot title.
        plot (bool): Whether to show the t-SNE embedding.

    Returns:
        dict: {
            "X_pca": (n_trials, n_components),
            "X_tsne": (n_trials, 2),
            "labels": (n_trials,)
        }
    """

    # === Select PCA output ===
    if use == "avg":
        X_pca = pca_results["pca_avg"] # uses  (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for avg input
    elif use == "flat":
        X_pca = pca_results["pca_flat"] # uses (n_trials, n_components) = PCA-transformed scores for flatt input
    else:
        raise ValueError("use either 'avg' or 'flat' !")

    labels = pca_results["labels"]

    # === Run t-SNE ===
    tsne = TSNE(
        n_components=2,
        perplexity=tsne_perplexity,
        learning_rate='auto',
        init='pca',
        random_state=random_state
    )
    X_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(X_pca)

    # === Visualization ===
    if plot:
        plt.figure(figsize=(7, 6))
        sc = plt.scatter(X_tsne[:, 0], X_tsne[:, 1], c=labels, cmap='coolwarm',
                         edgecolor='k', alpha=0.8)
        plt.title(f"{animal_id} t-SNE Embedding ({'Averaged' if use=='avg' else 'Flattened'})", fontsize=12, weight='bold')
        plt.xlabel('t-SNE 1')
        plt.ylabel('t-SNE 2')
        cbar = plt.colorbar(sc)
        cbar.set_ticks([0, 1])
        cbar.set_ticklabels(['Non-anticipatory', 'Anticipatory'])
        plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

    return {
        "X_pca": X_pca,
        "X_tsne": X_tsne,
        "labels": labels
    }
